stylometry: When dealing with Nonlinear Models, they are more realistic than Linear Models, but at the same time more complex. When using Linear Models, conventional solver will find the optimal solution. However with nonlinear models, conventional solver may find only a suboptimal solution. It may find only one solution (number) as the optimal choice. But with Nonlinear models, there may be more than one optimal choice. The conventional solver may only find a local maximum, which is only optimal for part of the model, whereas for nonlinear models a global maxima is more correct and optimal.
